<p>I was wondering how to find the setpoints needed for it to work, since setpoints are usually in angles.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-03-04T15:16:10.133Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":68,"reads":225,"readers_count":224,"score":385.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":494187,"topic_slug":"elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/Maeser8885/2025Bot/blob/master/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/ElevatorSubsystem.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"2025Bot/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/ElevatorSubsystem.java at master · Maeser8885/2025Bot · GitHub","clicks":8}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":73424,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches/494187/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3547187,"name":"","username":"crueter","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-04T15:19:41.791Z","cooked":"<p>You can get a conversion factor by running the elevator up a few inches (say 20-30), measure how many inches it is from its start point, and divide that number by the number of rotations the motor reports.</p>
<p>From there, you can multiply the encoder’s current rotation value by that factor to get inches, and divide the setpoint in inches by that factor to get rotations.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-03-04T15:19:41.791Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":218,"readers_count":217,"score":133.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":494187,"topic_slug":"elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":6}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50684,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6032 | QDash"},"post_url":"/t/elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches/494187/2","custom_user_title":"6032 | QDash","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":5},{"id":"+1","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":6,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3547216,"name":"","username":"CDL_066","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/c6cbf5/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-04T15:42:41.434Z","cooked":"<p>With a 2 stage elevator, the simple math for your conversion factor should be:</p>
<p>2(gear_ratio*(pi*sprocket_pitch_diameter))</p>
<p>So if you are using a 5:1 gear box with a 24T sprocket (1.92in), this becomes:</p>
<p>2*((3.141593*1.92)/5) = 2.4127</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-03-04T15:47:54.756Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":186,"readers_count":185,"score":52.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":494187,"topic_slug":"elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":16354,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches/494187/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"point_up","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3547219,"name":"","username":"team8885","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/e56c9b/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-04T15:45:44.878Z","cooked":"<p>And does my code work. This is my first time writing code for an elevator, so i just wanna make sure</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-03-04T15:45:44.878Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":158,"readers_count":157,"score":36.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":494187,"topic_slug":"elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":73424,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches/494187/4","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3547292,"name":"","username":"crueter","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-04T16:59:33.323Z","cooked":"<p>Looks good. Only things I would change would be to move the target variable into a parameter in your setpoint method, and also make a command for that setpoint method.</p>
<p>I would also make commands to run the motor forwards and backwards at a low speed, e.g. 0.4.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-03-04T16:59:33.323Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":138,"readers_count":137,"score":47.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":494187,"topic_slug":"elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":73424,"username":"team8885","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/e56c9b/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50684,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6032 | QDash"},"post_url":"/t/elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches/494187/5","custom_user_title":"6032 | QDash","reactions":[{"id":"+1","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3547299,"name":"","username":"Raysine","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/e495f1/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-04T17:01:46.082Z","cooked":"<p>We’re doing a similar thing using centimeters instead, but I ended using the motor shaft diameter times pi to get the circumference and am using that as my distance conversion. We haven’t been able to test that yet, but we will later today</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-03-04T17:01:46.082Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":125,"readers_count":124,"score":30.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":494187,"topic_slug":"elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":55669,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Lead programmer for 7160"},"post_url":"/t/elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches/494187/6","custom_user_title":"Lead programmer for 7160","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3547396,"name":"","username":"crueter","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-04T18:19:53.959Z","cooked":"<p>You also have to account for gear ratio and sprocket size.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-03-04T18:19:53.959Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":99,"readers_count":98,"score":19.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":494187,"topic_slug":"elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":55669,"username":"Raysine","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/e495f1/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50684,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6032 | QDash"},"post_url":"/t/elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches/494187/7","custom_user_title":"6032 | QDash","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548560,"name":"","username":"team8885","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/e56c9b/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T19:49:57.753Z","cooked":"<p>Also, with it, when I set the setpoint, will the grabber move after the elevator, or at the same time(its in robotcontainer)</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T19:49:57.753Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":69,"readers_count":68,"score":18.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":494187,"topic_slug":"elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":50684,"username":"crueter","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":73424,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches/494187/8","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548636,"name":"","username":"crueter","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T21:03:30.424Z","cooked":"<p>I assume you’re talking about these:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">//7 = intake
    m_driverController.button(7).onTrue(new InstantCommand(() -&gt; {
      elevatorSubsystem.setTargetCommand(Constants.ElevatorConstants.intakeSetpoint);
      grabberSubsystem.setTargetCommand(Constants.GrabberConstants.intakeSetpoint);
    }));
    //8 = L4
    m_driverController.button(8).onTrue(new InstantCommand(() -&gt; {
      elevatorSubsystem.setTargetCommand(Constants.ElevatorConstants.L4Setpoint);
      grabberSubsystem.setTargetCommand(Constants.GrabberConstants.L4Setpoint);
    }));
    //9 = L2
    m_driverController.button(9).onTrue(new InstantCommand(() -&gt; {
      elevatorSubsystem.setTargetCommand(Constants.ElevatorConstants.L2Setpoint);
      grabberSubsystem.setTargetCommand(Constants.GrabberConstants.L2Setpoint);
    }));
    //10 = L3
    m_driverController.button(10).onTrue(new InstantCommand(() -&gt; {
      elevatorSubsystem.setTargetCommand(Constants.ElevatorConstants.L3Setpoint);
      grabberSubsystem.setTargetCommand(Constants.GrabberConstants.L3Setpoint);
    }));
    //11 = DOWN
    m_driverController.button(11).onTrue(new InstantCommand(() -&gt; {
      elevatorSubsystem.setTargetCommand(Constants.ElevatorConstants.downSetpoint);
      grabberSubsystem.setTargetCommand(Constants.GrabberConstants.downSetpoint);
    }));
    //12 = L1
    m_driverController.button(12).onTrue(new InstantCommand(() -&gt; {
      elevatorSubsystem.setTargetCommand(Constants.ElevatorConstants.L1Setpoint);
      grabberSubsystem.setTargetCommand(Constants.GrabberConstants.L1Setpoint);
    }));
</code></pre>
<p>Since <code>setTargetCommand</code> returns a <code>Command</code>, you don’t want to run it like a subroutine; you instead want to bind these two together as a composition e.g.:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">m_driverController.button(10).onTrue(
    elevatorSubsystem.setTargetCommand(
        Constants.ElevatorConstants.L3Setpoint
    ).alongWith(
        grabberSubsystem.setTargetCommand(
            Constants.GrabberConstants.L3Setpoint)));
</code></pre>
<p>This will run the two at the same time. If you want the grabber to move after the elevator, change <code>alongWith</code> to <code>andThen</code>.</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T21:04:20.870Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":54,"readers_count":53,"score":15.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":494187,"topic_slug":"elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":73424,"username":"team8885","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/e56c9b/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50684,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6032 | QDash"},"post_url":"/t/elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches/494187/9","custom_user_title":"6032 | QDash","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3548769,"name":"","username":"team8885","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/e56c9b/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-05T23:40:56.496Z","cooked":"<p>oh ok thanks</p>","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-03-05T23:40:56.496Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":9,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":38,"readers_count":37,"score":22.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":494187,"topic_slug":"elevator-convert-rotations-to-inches","display_username":"","prima